Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.61,0:00:05.60,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我不再是 拍摄之前那个我了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.62,0:00:12.82,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,{\pos(390,473)}演员
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.82,0:00:14.66,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,演员和记者
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.66,0:00:16.80,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,大演员和大记者
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.73,0:00:17.03,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,{\move(465, 475, -100, 475)}大演员和大记者
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.26,0:00:21.82,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,乡下的秋天太阴郁了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.86,0:00:25.09,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我要是这么差 那我是怎么赚到钱的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.13,0:00:26.66,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,他是个病态的人
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.70,0:00:30.57,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 你跟他们说得各不相同 - 我听懂了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.48,0:00:37.88,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我与其中一个猴子确实有共鸣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.91,0:00:41.54,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你今天怎么打扮这么漂亮
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.58,0:00:44.68,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 《嘉士伯酒厂》- 不 我没演过
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.72,0:00:47.99,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我能问个问题吗
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.02,0:00:52.19,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我决定穿黑色 显瘦
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.23,0:00:55.13,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 《斗牛士》- 不 我还没出道
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.16,0:01:00.26,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 我首映的时候写的 - 我不记得了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.30,0:01:06.00,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,谁都可以自称演员 要是年薪百万的话
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.04,0:01:10.24,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,作者 导演 提尔 这些词联系在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.28,0:01:15.27,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,拉斯冯提尔懂得享受生活 他是个有活力有玩心的人
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.32,0:01:18.88,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,这部片中 他又一次戏弄了媒介
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.92,0:01:22.32,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,叫作"自动影像捕捉" 预制的画面
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.36,0:01:26.92,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,全由电脑决定 提尔让机器做主了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.96,0:01:29.43,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,极其古怪
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.46,0:01:34.30,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我第一次听到时 一点都他妈没听懂
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.34,0:01:38.67,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,是无穷的乐趣源泉 因为实在是太蠢了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.71,0:01:41.40,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你有大堆演员
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.44,0:01:44.41,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,然后摄像机选择拍一卷卫生纸
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.45,0:01:49.28,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我心想 "这一次他又要搞什么鬼"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.32,0:01:53.08,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,必须得有些约束在
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.12,0:01:58.53,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,6分钟长的卫生纸镜头 永远没机会用
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.36,0:02:04.82,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,下面这部电影 也许你已经看出有点怪异
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.87,0:02:08.96,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,那么坚持住 谁都看出来了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:11.77,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,艺术何时成为艺术
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.81,0:02:16.47,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,何时对话心灵 何时对话头脑
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.51,0:02:18.71,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Thes这些问题e questions are...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.75,0:02:23.88,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,这些是你看一部提尔的新片时 需要问的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.92,0:02:27.29,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,他刚刚创作了喜剧《真假老板》
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.32,0:02:34.35,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我们与演员们讨论了艺术 喜剧是轻松的 这是严肃的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.40,0:02:39.03,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,对你而言 在与你男友共事的同时
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.07,0:02:43.23,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,有这么大尺度的裸露 感受如何
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.27,0:02:46.80,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,有他在边上 你能适应吗
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.84,0:02:51.40,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,是的 我觉得能看到Casper作为一个
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.45,0:02:58.51,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,传统意义上的演员活跃起来 这样很好
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.99,0:03:05.46,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你够了吗
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.49,0:03:10.86,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- Iben 你的角色是主角 - 是的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.90,0:03:14.20,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,这需要大量的准备工作
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.24,0:03:18.23,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,闭嘴 你不说我们更生气
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.27,0:03:23.51,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 显然也是个高难度的角色 - 是的 可以这么说
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.55,0:03:29.81,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,她很有抱负 你知道 她真的想达到顶尖
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.85,0:03:35.12,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,来个像样的口活 不然就没得操
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.16,0:03:38.82,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,提尔把你的角色根植于你自己的生活
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.86,0:03:45.60,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,在电影中扮演你自己 是什么感受
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.63,0:03:49.63,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,在电影中扮演我自己
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.67,0:03:55.97,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,当然 我们利用自己的不同侧面 但我不是在扮演我自己
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.01,0:03:59.57,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 概括而言 你是说 - 是的 比如说
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.61,0:04:01.48,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.52,0:04:07.28,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 他很像你 不是吗 - 据提尔说 是这样的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.32,0:04:09.81,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,但我不太确定
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.86,0:04:13.99,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,他说你挺柔弱和反复无常的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.03,0:04:16.59,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你会这样看待自己吗
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.63,0:04:20.97,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,柔弱没有什么错 但是反复无常
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.00,0:04:23.80,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,来吧
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.84,0:04:28.87,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,起来啦 来抱抱
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.91,0:04:32.87,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你在台词方面帮助Casper 辅导他 我猜
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:37.01,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 这对你自己的角色有帮助吗 - 没有 我得说
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.05,0:04:41.01,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 我能不能 - 等一下 让我说完
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.06,0:04:45.69,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- Casper得从头学起 - 不 我没有
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.73,0:04:49.53,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,是的 你有 完全是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.56,0:04:53.93,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,说心里话 你在这种情境下就像个新生婴儿
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.97,0:04:58.53,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Sofie 你其中一场大戏是在动物园 猴子笼旁边
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.57,0:05:02.77,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,作为演员 你是如何动用环境
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.81,0:05:04.80,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,来塑造你的角色的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.41,0:05:10.68,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我和它们没什么对白 你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:14.09,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你觉得和那些猴子有什么共鸣吗
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.12,0:05:20.76,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,有点不好意思 但我不记得它们是什么了 狒狒吗
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.64,0:05:35.48,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Jens Albinus 你和提尔一起演过戏 这次怎么样呢
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.21,0:05:40.24,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,这个问题我没听懂
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.28,0:05:44.05,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 你认识他 - 我没和他一起演过戏
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.09,0:05:48.04,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,没人告诉我你会问这个
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.09,0:05:52.12,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我的意思是 你演过提尔的电影
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:55.49,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,噢是的 对
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.53,0:05:59.59,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,但是这次不一样
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.63,0:06:03.93,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 完全不一样 - 怎么说
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.97,0:06:11.47,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我只能说 这和某些个演员有关系
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:17.38,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我的经验基础相当多 你知道的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.42,0:06:22.41,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我已经开创了我自己的方法 我称之为Gantzler方法
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.46,0:06:28.29,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,因此当我接到一个新角色 我清楚地知道如何展现
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.33,0:06:32.39,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,而这个家伙 Ravn 也不例外
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.43,0:06:38.07,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,他叫Ravn (渡鸦) 是种鸟类 这就是突破口
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.11,0:06:45.04,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Ravn Ravn Ravn
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.08,0:06:48.17,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 你没觉得缺乏安全感吗 - 没那么严重
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:53.45,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我没有像个白痴一样跑来跑去 说着你那些多愁善感的胡话
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.49,0:06:57.02,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 你以为你是谁 - 我在说实话
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.06,0:07:01.26,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你什么都不懂 你就噼里啪啦走过来
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.30,0:07:04.73,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,"我要去让拉斯冯提尔见识见识"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:10.03,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 好吧 我做到了啊 - 不 你没有 你就坐在那儿
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.07,0:07:14.03,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,要不是我 你看着就像个呆子了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.08,0:07:16.20,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,就差这么一点了 你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.58,0:07:23.98,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你能具体一点吗 你想说的是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.02,0:07:26.85,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你得小心说话
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.89,0:07:31.38,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Peter  你对于Gantzler方法十分坦率
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.43,0:07:36.89,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,这是你和提尔一路讨论着要开发出来
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.93,0:07:40.99,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,的技巧手法吗
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.04,0:07:47.10,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,让我这么说吧 有一点是绝对肯定的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.14,0:07:53.24,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,拉斯知道我有这么一种特殊技巧
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.28,0:07:57.45,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我们没有讨论过那么多 个人而言 我不喜欢
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.49,0:08:01.95,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,让别人在我的技巧上指指点点
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.99,0:08:05.22,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,但是我听其他的人说过
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.26,0:08:09.29,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,拉斯给过我很高的评价
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.33,0:08:12.82,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,不止作为个人 也是作为演员
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.87,0:08:15.80,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,他把这种方法说得非常有价值
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:19.50,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,对不起 对不起
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.54,0:08:23.84,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,要是你认为自己有半点才华  你想带着这种空洞的看法过下去
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.88,0:08:26.44,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,那也没问题
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.48,0:08:30.54,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我才不听你这种屁话 我要出去
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.19,0:08:43.46,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,恐惧即诗意 诗意即恐惧 这两者在艺术的世界里
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.50,0:08:47.09,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,在提尔的世界里 紧密相连
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.14,0:08:50.87,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,许多演员将恐惧作为一种驱力
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.91,0:08:55.00,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,所以你可以问 "恐惧是否一种驱力"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.04,0:08:58.88,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Louise 你在拍摄过程中害怕吗
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.82,0:09:08.45,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 是的 她害怕 - 一点点
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.49,0:09:11.93,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 什么 - 你为什么要那么说
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.96,0:09:17.36,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,作为演员 你总是在害怕做得不够好
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.40,0:09:22.67,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,不被人喜欢 这就是你为什么会做这个 你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.70,0:09:25.14,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 你也害怕吗 - 是的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.17,0:09:27.23,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,是的 她害怕
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.28,0:09:34.06,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你总是在开玩笑 有时候让我困惑
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.22,0:09:38.28,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,分不清你是不是在开玩笑 我没法回复
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:42.31,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你有过和猴子合作的经验吗
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.36,0:09:46.62,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,是的 我有 我以前试过
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.66,0:09:51.26,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,在这种情况下 你有什么要求要提吗
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.30,0:09:56.46,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,"这一次我不想碰猴子了"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.50,0:10:00.60,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,没有 你是想说 这次我是否想要不同的动物吗
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.64,0:10:03.87,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,是的 或者和猴子的接触 很简单
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.38,0:10:07.11,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 什么 - 你不想要这种接触
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.15,0:10:13.75,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,不 不能这么说 他选择猴子是有原因的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:18.45,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,如果这样对这场戏最好 那我没问题
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.49,0:10:22.05,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,这整个演艺行业都空洞得不可思议
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:26.23,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,这不是种你能学会的东西 你要么行 要么不行
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.27,0:10:29.60,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我认为Iben行 她很有才华
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.64,0:10:33.40,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,但她年纪大了 所以她不能挑挑拣拣
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.51,0:10:42.54,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,时机不是种你能在学校学会的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.58,0:10:48.04,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,所以他们国家电影学院那些屁话
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.09,0:10:51.75,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,跑来跑去 什么"你能感受到这些沙子吗"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.79,0:10:56.59,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,而那里根本没什么该死的沙子 你是想唬弄谁
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.63,0:11:02.26,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我做演员已经16年了 演过15-20部电影
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.30,0:11:07.50,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 我在想《瓦尔特与卡洛》- 不 那不是我
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.54,0:11:10.77,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你知道我的名字吗
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.81,0:11:17.68,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我有一种罕见的能力 仅凭想着什么东西
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.72,0:11:21.82,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,就能影响我身边的人
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.86,0:11:26.88,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,因此 如果我看到一个演员不太行
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.93,0:11:31.46,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我可以通过意念传送点导演诀窍给拉斯
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:35.49,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,他就可以传达过去 通常都很成功
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.54,0:11:41.17,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Peter Gantzler是一个病得非常非常重的人 非常非常重
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.21,0:11:44.84,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 你是什么意思- 还是不要说了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.88,0:11:50.08,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Peter Gantzler 一个病人 他只是个演员 不是吗
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:56.15,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我才是导演 你只是演员
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.19,0:12:01.72,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我嗅到你的恐惧背后有故事 是什么故事
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.67,0:12:07.69,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,这
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.74,0:12:12.50,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我还是不要了说 不要说
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.04,0:12:17.67,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,哇
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.71,0:12:21.67,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你一定害怕自动影像捕捉来着吧
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.72,0:12:25.88,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,其实我们发明了一种叫作"自动表演"的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.92,0:12:30.08,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,非常类似 当你提出一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.12,0:12:36.22,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你以为会得到相应的答案 但其实不会
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.26,0:12:44.57,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,作为演员 恐惧是你必备的工具之一吗 这样说
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.61,0:12:48.63,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,不 我想不是 我想
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.68,0:12:53.61,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,好吧 食堂吃的还挺多种多样 你不觉得吗
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.65,0:12:59.02,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,就是 就是一天中的高潮 你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.05,0:13:03.96,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,不论你是否得到了满足
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.99,0:13:06.93,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,食物方面
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.96,0:13:12.26,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,重点在于你是否有计划 就是这个
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.30,0:13:17.80,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,要是你浪费了4年 到处鬼混 喝喝啤酒
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.84,0:13:22.83,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,穿什么颜色的拖鞋跳跳舞 难怪你这么刻薄
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.88,0:13:28.18,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,看到其他人高中毕业也混得不错的时候 你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.22,0:13:33.45,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你演过什么电影
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.49,0:13:37.19,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,太多了 我没法全记住
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.23,0:13:42.63,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,有… 我也拒绝过一大堆
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.66,0:13:45.06,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你害怕的是提尔吗
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.28,0:14:00.58,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,哪方面让你觉得提尔是一个作者导演
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.83,0:14:14.39,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,问我点别的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.43,0:14:20.39,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,提尔打来电话的时候 你是不是想 "提尔 就是说奖项"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.43,0:14:24.23,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- "这能让我再拿个奖" - 是的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.27,0:14:29.51,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,要是我们谈票房和评分
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.54,0:14:33.78,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,或者周刊杂志上的"年度电视"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.81,0:14:37.48,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我不知道你是否想谈那些 但要是你想
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.52,0:14:40.28,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,那么是的 我们都拿过奖
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.32,0:14:45.35,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,你留意到我们拍完这部片后 西兰岛北部
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.39,0:14:49.49,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,剧烈的天气变化了吗
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.53,0:14:53.30,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 什么 - 我住在北部那边
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.33,0:14:57.46,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我花园里的天气 再也不一样了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.51,0:15:01.67,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 这和Gantzler有什么关系 - 问他去啊
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.44,0:15:06.44,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,所有演员并不都是同等地敏锐 你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.48,0:15:09.21,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,而这部片的选角
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.25,0:15:14.69,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,我没时间给拉斯具体的指示
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:19.06,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,关于各个角色我想选谁
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.09,0:15:24.62,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,所以他选出来的就有点 不全可靠
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.67,0:15:28.10,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,但是 人都会犯错
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.14,0:15:34.23,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,但这很困难 尤其是
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.28,0:15:36.21,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Jens那边
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.24,0:15:40.27,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,I've got this spot between\Nthe second and third vertebrae
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.31,0:15:43.22,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,which hasn't been the same since.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.25,0:15:47.48,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,And every time I hear his name\Nit gets worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:50.68,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,God, I'm furious!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.50,0:15:58.73,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Ravn is the key character,\Nso it's important to me
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.77,0:16:04.83,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,that Jens respects the fact that\NI'm the star, and follows my lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.87,0:16:09.24,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,That was hard for him.\NHe clearly has no method whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:16.01,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,He's out of a very different,\Nmore clownlike tradition, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.05,0:16:20.18,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,It's terribly difficult\Nto work with sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.39,0:16:27.92,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,You're just acting scared now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:31.90,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right. I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.93,0:16:38.03,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,We're just acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.07,0:16:41.37,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,That's an actor's specialty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.41,0:16:45.64,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- Were you in "The Idiots"?\N- Yes, I was, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.68,0:16:48.84,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- Have you seen it?\N- I've seen some clips.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.88,0:16:54.19,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- We don't see all the films.\N- No, of course. There are so many.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.22,0:16:57.19,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Of course I do. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.22,0:17:03.39,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Do you go for both the Bodil and\NRobert Awards when you choose a part?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.43,0:17:07.99,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,No. I go for\Nthe Bodil Award, primarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.44,0:17:15.21,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- How believable was that line?\N- Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.24,0:17:20.18,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,The Robert Awards are a bit\Nmore unpredictable, to be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.21,0:17:25.38,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,They're harder to plan for.\NIt seems very random.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.42,0:17:29.58,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,You can look at something\Nand say, "This is Bodil material"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.62,0:17:32.65,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.69,0:17:35.89,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Didn't you feel\Nlike an outsider sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.93,0:17:41.10,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes. I can't be so narcissistic,\Nstare at myself in the mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.14,0:17:44.83,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,and do my hair for hours\Nlike Peter Gantzler did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.87,0:17:49.00,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,But I've had other experiences\Nthat they haven't had
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.04,0:17:53.24,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,because they were up in some loft,\Ndoing improvisations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.28,0:17:58.08,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,The rest of us were out there\Ndoing stand-up and making big money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.12,0:18:01.49,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,We're talking free drinks,\Nfull throttle,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.52,0:18:06.29,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,chicks and the rest of it.\NThat's what makes a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.33,0:18:13.53,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,You can't ask more of a man than\Nwhat he can give. In that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.57,0:18:18.47,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,I felt sorry for Jens.\NHe clearly wasn't up to the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.51,0:18:25.74,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,And it's true that I taunted him\Nsometimes. Put him in his place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.78,0:18:31.74,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Would you feel better if we didn't\Ntalk about Peter Gantzler at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:37.75,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- That's probably the best thing.\N- Jens, this movie...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.79,0:18:41.25,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,No, stop it.\NI can't do it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.30,0:18:45.86,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Trier's movies are very arty-farty,\NI guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.90,0:18:50.46,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,But Trier is an extremely\Ninsecure man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.50,0:18:56.77,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,When he meets someone like me\Nwho isn't, he attaches himself to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.81,0:19:00.94,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,He calls me and says,\N"What do I do? I don't want to fly."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.98,0:19:05.38,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,I tell him,\N"Goddamn it, Trier. Drive!"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.42,0:19:11.09,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,You don't get that look from the\Nothers, "She's won a lot of awards"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.13,0:19:15.03,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- You'll have to ask them.\N- You don't feel it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.06,0:19:17.83,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,I think I choose to shut it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.87,0:19:21.80,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Hasn't Trier won more awards\Nthan me? He must have.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.37,0:19:27.40,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say I'm his mentor\Nor coach. I'm more a kind of rock
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.44,0:19:33.21,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,on which he can place\Nhis film genius, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.25,0:19:37.62,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- You bring Trier into a new era?\N- No, he does that himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.65,0:19:43.85,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,But we all know that if Iron Maiden\Nplay a concert in Edinburgh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.89,0:19:47.59,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,they do the performing,\Nbut how did they get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.63,0:19:52.50,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,With your enormous\Nmental resources...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.53,0:19:56.30,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- I think it's safe to say that?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.34,0:20:00.90,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,The resources that you have,\Nin this situation as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.94,0:20:04.78,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Right now? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.81,0:20:10.68,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,If you were to draw on that to give\NLars von Trier some advice
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.72,0:20:15.42,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,to take with him\Non his journey,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.46,0:20:21.16,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,what would it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.20,0:20:25.69,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,"When you can't be like me, Lars,\Njust be yourself."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.94,0:20:31.53,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.57,0:20:34.51,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,What's been\Nyour best advice to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.54,0:20:37.53,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,It must have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.58,0:20:41.24,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,"Deep breaths, Lars.\NJust get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.28,0:20:45.91,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Forget about doing\Nnew things all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.95,0:20:47.94,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Drop it. Let's have some fun."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.99,0:20:54.76,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,When people look back at my films\Nin a hundred years' time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.80,0:21:01.56,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,they'll probably say, "Bloody hell!\NThat guy knew what he was doing."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.60,0:21:06.73,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,I'll just go and check\Nthat Iben is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.77,0:21:09.87,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,She's got the car keys, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.91,0:21:16.15,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- Don't you have any more questions?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.18,0:21:18.98,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,We're just acting, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.02,0:21:22.55,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- Are you acting?\N- Yes. Couldn't you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.59,0:21:28.22,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- No.\N- Great acting. I really tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.84,0:21:41.90,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,You've experienced it for yourself.\NThe insight into the world of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.94,0:21:46.14,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Powerlessness, power.\NJoy, enthusiasm, feelings... fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.18,0:21:51.78,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Reality, parallel reality...\NThank you for watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.82,0:22:00.39,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,When you turn up in the morning,\Nready to shoot some scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.43,0:22:05.30,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,it's like entering...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.33,0:22:09.70,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- different rooms.\N- What rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.74,0:22:14.61,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,And one of those rooms\Nthat you're constantly in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.64,0:22:20.01,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,is the room filled with fear,\NI guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.05,0:22:24.11,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to do\Nthe interview that we agreed on,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.15,0:22:29.45,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,you can say whatever\Nyou want. I'm leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.49,0:22:33.09,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.13,0:22:37.46,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,You can't help laughing\Nwhen you're fearful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.50,0:22:40.49,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,That's perfect. Brilliant.\NCut!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.57,0:25:55.56,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Why does he ask me that?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.18,0:29:04.11,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,There was a bit more nonsense\Nin this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.15,0:29:06.91,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- I'm so involved with my work.\N- That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.95,0:29:09.94,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- "Pip."\N- "Pip."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.99,0:29:11.78,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,He's fabulous.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.53,0:29:21.22,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Let me just have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.55,0:32:36.08,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- And this one is all of the text?\N- Yes, it's those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.13,0:32:38.22,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,I'll get these onto some cardboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.26,0:32:43.10,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,"And even though I may seem\Nlike a reflection, this film is not."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.13,0:32:50.47,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,I'm happy with it.\NThat's a punch right in their faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.51,0:32:55.31,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Put it there,\Nand I'll go up and have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.34,0:32:58.54,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Put one here by my finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.58,0:33:01.57,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- That's nothing.\N- There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.76,0:33:16.03,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,I'd like a movement going\Ndiagonally across the windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.20,0:33:22.36,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,This is some toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.40,0:33:29.07,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,If this looks odd already, please stay,\Nbecause it won't be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.60,0:36:33.09,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- That's good.\N- It's super! That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.57,0:37:09.27,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- 13 degrees to the left.\N- That won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.31,0:37:15.08,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,- It's the wrong direction.\N- Let's have a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.95,0:37:53.28,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Tilt down 11 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.32,0:37:58.78,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,And 33 centimeters to the left.\NYou'll like this, Lars.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.83,0:38:03.56,Chinese-480P,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're happy, I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.61,0:00:05.60,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I'm not the same person\Nthat I was before the shooting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.62,0:00:12.99,English-480P,,0,0,0,,THE ACTORS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.02,0:00:17.22,English-480P,,0,0,0,,AND THE JOURNALIST\NOF IT ALL
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.26,0:00:21.82,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Autumn in the country\Ncan be really muggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.86,0:00:25.09,English-480P,,0,0,0,,If I'm so bad, then how come\NI take home the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.13,0:00:26.66,English-480P,,0,0,0,,He's a sick man.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.70,0:00:30.57,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Have you said different things?\N- I understand the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.48,0:00:37.88,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I do connect\Nwith one of the monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.91,0:00:41.54,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Why are you so dressed up today?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.58,0:00:44.68,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- "Bryggeren"?\N- No, I wasn't in that either.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.72,0:00:47.99,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.02,0:00:52.19,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I decided to wear black.\NIt makes you look thinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.23,0:00:55.13,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- "Matador"?\N- No. Before my time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.16,0:01:00.26,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- I wore it at the premiere.\N- I can't remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.30,0:01:06.00,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Anyone can call himself an actor\Nif he earns a million a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.04,0:01:10.24,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Auteur, director, Trier...\Nthe words are connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.28,0:01:15.27,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Lars von Trier has joie de vivre.\NHe's a vibrant and playful man.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.32,0:01:18.88,English-480P,,0,0,0,,In this movie, he plays\Nwith the medium once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.92,0:01:22.32,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It's called "Automavision."\NPre-fabricated images.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.36,0:01:26.92,English-480P,,0,0,0,,A computer has planned it all.\NTrier has let the machine decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.96,0:01:29.43,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Utterly weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.46,0:01:34.30,English-480P,,0,0,0,,When I first heard about it\NI didn't understand a damned thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.34,0:01:38.67,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It was a constant source of fun\Nbecause it's so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.71,0:01:41.40,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You have lots of actors,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.44,0:01:44.41,English-480P,,0,0,0,,and then the camera\Nopts to film a kitchen roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.45,0:01:49.28,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I thought, "What the hell\Nis he up to this time?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.32,0:01:53.08,English-480P,,0,0,0,,There had to be some obstructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.12,0:01:58.53,English-480P,,0,0,0,,6 minutes' worth of kitchen roll\Nfootage which will never be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.36,0:02:04.82,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Here's a new film.\NIt may look strange to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.87,0:02:08.96,English-480P,,0,0,0,,but hang in there. There's\Nsomething for everyone, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:11.77,English-480P,,0,0,0,,When does art become art?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.81,0:02:16.47,English-480P,,0,0,0,,When does it speak to the heart,\Nwhen does it speak to the mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.51,0:02:18.71,English-480P,,0,0,0,,These questions are...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.75,0:02:23.88,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Those are questions you have to ask\Nwhen you see a new Trier movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.92,0:02:27.29,English-480P,,0,0,0,,He's just made the comedy\N"The Boss of It AII."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.32,0:02:34.35,English-480P,,0,0,0,,We've talked to the actors about art.\NComedy is fun. This is serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.40,0:02:39.03,English-480P,,0,0,0,,What was it like for you\Nto expose yourself so much
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.07,0:02:43.23,English-480P,,0,0,0,,while also working with your\Nboyfriend, Casper Christensen?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.27,0:02:46.80,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Could you cope,\Nwith him on the sideline?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.84,0:02:51.40,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NI thought it was great to see
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.45,0:02:58.51,English-480P,,0,0,0,,how Casper came alive as an actor\Nin a more classical sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.99,0:03:05.46,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Are you done now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.49,0:03:10.86,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Iben, your part is a major one.\N- Yes. It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.90,0:03:14.20,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It's required\Na lot of preparation work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.24,0:03:18.23,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Shut up. We'll be\Nmore upset if you don't tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.27,0:03:23.51,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- And clearly a difficult one.\N- Yes, and you could say...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.55,0:03:29.81,English-480P,,0,0,0,,She's ambitious, you know.\NShe really wants to reach the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.85,0:03:35.12,English-480P,,0,0,0,,There'll be no banging\Nuntil you've had a good licking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.16,0:03:38.82,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Trier has based your character\Non your own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.86,0:03:45.60,English-480P,,0,0,0,,What's it like,\Nplaying yourself in a movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.63,0:03:49.63,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Playing myself in a movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.67,0:03:55.97,English-480P,,0,0,0,,We use different sides of ourselves,\Nof course, but I'm not playing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.01,0:03:59.57,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Overall, you mean?\N- Yes, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.61,0:04:01.48,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.52,0:04:07.28,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- He resembles you, doesn't he?\N- According to Trier, he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.32,0:04:09.81,English-480P,,0,0,0,,But I'm not so sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.86,0:04:13.99,English-480P,,0,0,0,,He says you're quite soft\Nand inconsistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.03,0:04:16.59,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Do you see yourself that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.63,0:04:20.97,English-480P,,0,0,0,,There's nothing wrong\Nwith being soft, but inconsistent...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.00,0:04:23.80,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.84,0:04:28.87,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Up you go. That's it.\NBig hug.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.91,0:04:32.87,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You helped Casper with his lines\Nand coached him, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:37.01,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Did that help your own character?\N- No, I have to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.05,0:04:41.01,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Can I...?\N- Hold on. Let me finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.06,0:04:45.69,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Casper had to start from scratch.\N- No, I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.73,0:04:49.53,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes, you did. Completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.56,0:04:53.93,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Mentally speaking, you're like\Na newborn baby in this context.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.97,0:04:58.53,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Sofie, one of your big scenes\Nis in the zoo, at the monkey cage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.57,0:05:02.77,English-480P,,0,0,0,,What do you do as an actor\Nto use the environment
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.81,0:05:04.80,English-480P,,0,0,0,,and draw on that for your part?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.41,0:05:10.68,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I didn't have any dialogue\Nwith them, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:14.09,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Did you feel any connection\Nwith the monkey?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.12,0:05:20.76,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It's embarrassing, but I can't\Nremember what they are. Baboons?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.64,0:05:35.48,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Jens Albinus, you've played with\NTrier before. How was it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.21,0:05:40.24,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I don't understand the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.28,0:05:44.05,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- You know him.\N- I've never played with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.09,0:05:48.04,English-480P,,0,0,0,,No one has told me\Nyou would ask about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.09,0:05:52.12,English-480P,,0,0,0,,What I meant was, you've\Nbeen in a Trier movie before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:55.49,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes. Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.53,0:05:59.59,English-480P,,0,0,0,,But it was different\Nthis time around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.63,0:06:03.93,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- It was completely different.\N- In what way?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.97,0:06:11.47,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Let me just say that it has to do\Nwith certain members of the cast.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:17.38,English-480P,,0,0,0,,My base of experience\Nis enormous, as you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.42,0:06:22.41,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I've created my own method...\Nthe Gantzler Method as I call it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.46,0:06:28.29,English-480P,,0,0,0,,so that when I get a new part\NI know exactly how to approach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.33,0:06:32.39,English-480P,,0,0,0,,And this guy, Ravn,\Nwas no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.43,0:06:38.07,English-480P,,0,0,0,,He's called Ravn ("raven").\NIt's a bird. There's your opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.11,0:06:45.04,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Ravn, Ravn, Ravn...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.08,0:06:48.17,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- You haven't felt insecure?\N- Not that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:53.45,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I don't run around like an idiot\Nwith all your touchy-feely crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.49,0:06:57.02,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Who do you think you are?\N- I tell it like it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.06,0:07:01.26,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You don't know anything.\NYou just come stomping in...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.30,0:07:04.73,English-480P,,0,0,0,,"I'll go in and impress\NLars von Trier..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:10.03,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Well, it works.\N- No, it doesn't! You just sit there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.07,0:07:14.03,English-480P,,0,0,0,,If it hadn't been for me\Nyou would have looked like a dork.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.08,0:07:16.20,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You're this close, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.58,0:07:23.98,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Can you be more specific?\NWhat is it you want to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.02,0:07:26.85,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You have to watch what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.89,0:07:31.38,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Peter, you're being very candid\Nabout the Gantzler Method.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.43,0:07:36.89,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Was it a technical handle\Nthat you and Trier talked about
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.93,0:07:40.99,English-480P,,0,0,0,,developing along the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.04,0:07:47.10,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Let me put it this way.\NI'm absolutely certain that Lars
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.14,0:07:53.24,English-480P,,0,0,0,,was aware that I had\Nthis very special technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.28,0:07:57.45,English-480P,,0,0,0,,We didn't discuss it that much.\NPersonally, I don't like
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.49,0:08:01.95,English-480P,,0,0,0,,having people poke around\Nin my techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.99,0:08:05.22,English-480P,,0,0,0,,But I've heard\Nthrough other people
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.26,0:08:09.29,English-480P,,0,0,0,,that Lars has talked about me\Nin very positive terms...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.33,0:08:12.82,English-480P,,0,0,0,,not just as an individual,\Nbut also as an actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.87,0:08:15.80,English-480P,,0,0,0,,He described the method\Nas being very valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:19.50,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.54,0:08:23.84,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It's fine if you want to walk\Nthrough life with the hollow idea
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.88,0:08:26.44,English-480P,,0,0,0,,that you have any talent at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.48,0:08:30.54,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I'm not listening to this shit.\NI'd like to get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.19,0:08:43.46,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Fear is poetry, poetry is fear.\NThe two are closely linked
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.50,0:08:47.09,English-480P,,0,0,0,,in the world of art,\Nin the world of Trier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.14,0:08:50.87,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Many actors use fear\Nas a driving force.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.91,0:08:55.00,English-480P,,0,0,0,,So you could ask,\N"Is fear a driving force?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.04,0:08:58.88,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Louise, were you afraid\Nduring the filming?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.82,0:09:08.45,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes, she was. A bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.49,0:09:11.93,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- What?\N- Why do you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.96,0:09:17.36,English-480P,,0,0,0,,As an actor, you're always afraid\Nof not being good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.40,0:09:22.67,English-480P,,0,0,0,,And not being loved.\NThat's why we do it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.70,0:09:25.14,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Were you afraid as well?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.17,0:09:27.23,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes. She was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.28,0:09:34.18,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You joke a lot. Sometimes\NI don't know exactly what to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.22,0:09:38.28,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I can't respond when I don't\Nknow if it was a joke or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:42.31,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Do you have any experience\Nin working with monkeys?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.36,0:09:46.62,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes, I have.\NI've tried it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.66,0:09:51.26,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Do you make any demands\Nin that sort of situation:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.30,0:09:56.46,English-480P,,0,0,0,,"This time I don't want\Nto touch the monkey"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.50,0:10:00.60,English-480P,,0,0,0,,No. Did I want different animals\Nthis time, you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.64,0:10:03.87,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes, or contact with the monkeys,\Nquite simply.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.38,0:10:07.11,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Sorry?\N- That you didn't want that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.15,0:10:13.75,English-480P,,0,0,0,,No, I can't say that. There's\Na reason why he chose monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:18.45,English-480P,,0,0,0,,If that's what's best for the scene,\Nthen I'm ready to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.49,0:10:22.05,English-480P,,0,0,0,,The whole acting business\Nis incredibly hollow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:26.23,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It's not something you can learn.\NYou either have it, or you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.27,0:10:29.60,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I think Iben's got it.\NShe's really talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.64,0:10:33.40,English-480P,,0,0,0,,But she's getting older,\Nso she can't pick and choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.51,0:10:42.54,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Timing isn't something\Nyou can learn in a school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.58,0:10:48.04,English-480P,,0,0,0,,So all their National School\Nof Theatre crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.09,0:10:51.75,English-480P,,0,0,0,,running around, going\N"Can you feel the sand?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.79,0:10:56.59,English-480P,,0,0,0,,when there isn't any goddamn sand.\NWho are you trying to fool?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.63,0:11:02.26,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I've been an actor for 16 years.\NI've been in 15-20 films.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.30,0:11:07.50,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- I'm thinking "Walter and Carlo"?\N- No, that wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.54,0:11:10.77,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Do you even know my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.81,0:11:17.68,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I've got the rare ability\Nto influence people around me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.72,0:11:21.82,English-480P,,0,0,0,,just by thinking certain things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.86,0:11:26.88,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if I see an actor\Nwho hasn't quite got it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.93,0:11:31.46,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I can mentally transfer\Ndirection tips to Lars,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:35.49,English-480P,,0,0,0,,which he can then pass on.\NUsually with great success.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.54,0:11:41.17,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Peter Gantzler is\Na very, very sick man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.21,0:11:44.84,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- What do you mean by that?\N- Let's not get into that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.88,0:11:50.08,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Peter Gantzler, a sick man?\NHe's just an actor, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:56.15,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It's a good thing that I'm\Nthe director, and you're just an actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.19,0:12:01.72,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I sense a story behind your fear.\NWhat is that story about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.67,0:12:07.69,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.74,0:12:12.50,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I'd rather not talk about it.\NDon't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.04,0:12:17.67,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Gosh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.71,0:12:21.67,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You must have been\Nafraid of Automavision?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.72,0:12:25.88,English-480P,,0,0,0,,We've actually invented this thing\Ncalled "Automa-action."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.92,0:12:30.08,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It's very similar.\NWhen you pose a question,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.12,0:12:36.22,English-480P,,0,0,0,,you think you're getting the\Ncorresponding answer, but you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.26,0:12:44.57,English-480P,,0,0,0,,As an actor, does fear have to be\Npart of your toolbox, so to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.61,0:12:48.63,English-480P,,0,0,0,,No, I don't think so.\NI think...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.68,0:12:53.61,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Well... the canteen food\Nwas quite varied, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.65,0:12:59.02,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It was... It was the highlight\Nof the day, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.05,0:13:03.96,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Whether or not\Nyou got any satisfaction...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.99,0:13:06.93,English-480P,,0,0,0,,foodwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.96,0:13:12.26,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It's about whether or not\Nyou project. That's the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.30,0:13:17.80,English-480P,,0,0,0,,If you've wasted four years,\Nfucking around, drinking beer,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.84,0:13:22.83,English-480P,,0,0,0,,trying to dance a certain color\Nin slippers... no wonder you're bitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.88,0:13:28.18,English-480P,,0,0,0,,When the rest of us can get by\Njust with high school, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.22,0:13:33.45,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Which films have you been in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.49,0:13:37.19,English-480P,,0,0,0,,There are so many.\NI can't remember them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.23,0:13:42.63,English-480P,,0,0,0,,There's been... I've said no\Nto a lot of things as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.66,0:13:45.06,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Is it Trier you're afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.28,0:14:00.58,English-480P,,0,0,0,,In what way do you feel\Nthat Trier is an auteur?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.83,0:14:14.39,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Ask me about something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.43,0:14:20.39,English-480P,,0,0,0,,When Trier calls you do you think,\N"Trier... that means awards"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.43,0:14:24.23,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- "This will get me another award"?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.27,0:14:29.51,English-480P,,0,0,0,,If we talk ticket sales\Nor ratings
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.54,0:14:33.78,English-480P,,0,0,0,,or "TV Host of The Year"\Nin the weekly magazines...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.81,0:14:37.48,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you want to go\Nthere, but if you do...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.52,0:14:40.28,English-480P,,0,0,0,,then yes, we've all won awards.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.32,0:14:45.35,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Have you noticed the drastic change\Nin the North Zealand weather
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.39,0:14:49.49,English-480P,,0,0,0,,after we shot this movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.53,0:14:53.30,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- What?\N- I live in the northern part.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.33,0:14:57.46,English-480P,,0,0,0,,The weather in my garden\Nhasn't been the same since.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.51,0:15:01.67,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- What's it got to do with Gantzler?\N- Well, ask him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.44,0:15:06.44,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Not all actors are equally\Nresponsive, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.48,0:15:09.21,English-480P,,0,0,0,,And the casting on this film...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.25,0:15:14.69,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I didn't have time to give Lars\Nspecific instructions about
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:19.06,English-480P,,0,0,0,,who I would like to see\Nin the various parts,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.09,0:15:24.62,English-480P,,0,0,0,,so his choices are a bit...\Nshaky in places.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.67,0:15:28.10,English-480P,,0,0,0,,But... to err is human.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.14,0:15:34.23,English-480P,,0,0,0,,But it was difficult,\Nespecially with...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.28,0:15:36.21,English-480P,,0,0,0,,with Jens.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.24,0:15:40.27,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I've got this spot between\Nthe second and third vertebrae
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.31,0:15:43.22,English-480P,,0,0,0,,which hasn't been the same since.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.25,0:15:47.48,English-480P,,0,0,0,,And every time I hear his name\Nit gets worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:50.68,English-480P,,0,0,0,,God, I'm furious!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.50,0:15:58.73,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Ravn is the key character,\Nso it's important to me
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.77,0:16:04.83,English-480P,,0,0,0,,that Jens respects the fact that\NI'm the star, and follows my lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.87,0:16:09.24,English-480P,,0,0,0,,That was hard for him.\NHe clearly has no method whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:16.01,English-480P,,0,0,0,,He's out of a very different,\Nmore clownlike tradition, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.05,0:16:20.18,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It's terribly difficult\Nto work with sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.39,0:16:27.92,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You're just acting scared now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:31.90,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right. I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.93,0:16:38.03,English-480P,,0,0,0,,We're just acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.07,0:16:41.37,English-480P,,0,0,0,,That's an actor's specialty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.41,0:16:45.64,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Were you in "The Idiots"?\N- Yes, I was, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.68,0:16:48.84,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Have you seen it?\N- I've seen some clips.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.88,0:16:54.19,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- We don't see all the films.\N- No, of course. There are so many.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.22,0:16:57.19,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Of course I do. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.22,0:17:03.39,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Do you go for both the Bodil and\NRobert Awards when you choose a part?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.43,0:17:07.99,English-480P,,0,0,0,,No. I go for\Nthe Bodil Award, primarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.44,0:17:15.21,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- How believable was that line?\N- Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.24,0:17:20.18,English-480P,,0,0,0,,The Robert Awards are a bit\Nmore unpredictable, to be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.21,0:17:25.38,English-480P,,0,0,0,,They're harder to plan for.\NIt seems very random.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.42,0:17:29.58,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You can look at something\Nand say, "This is Bodil material"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.62,0:17:32.65,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.69,0:17:35.89,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Didn't you feel\Nlike an outsider sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.93,0:17:41.10,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes. I can't be so narcissistic,\Nstare at myself in the mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.14,0:17:44.83,English-480P,,0,0,0,,and do my hair for hours\Nlike Peter Gantzler did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.87,0:17:49.00,English-480P,,0,0,0,,But I've had other experiences\Nthat they haven't had
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.04,0:17:53.24,English-480P,,0,0,0,,because they were up in some loft,\Ndoing improvisations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.28,0:17:58.08,English-480P,,0,0,0,,The rest of us were out there\Ndoing stand-up and making big money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.12,0:18:01.49,English-480P,,0,0,0,,We're talking free drinks,\Nfull throttle,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.52,0:18:06.29,English-480P,,0,0,0,,chicks and the rest of it.\NThat's what makes a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.33,0:18:13.53,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You can't ask more of a man than\Nwhat he can give. In that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.57,0:18:18.47,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I felt sorry for Jens.\NHe clearly wasn't up to the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.51,0:18:25.74,English-480P,,0,0,0,,And it's true that I taunted him\Nsometimes. Put him in his place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.78,0:18:31.74,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Would you feel better if we didn't\Ntalk about Peter Gantzler at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:37.75,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- That's probably the best thing.\N- Jens, this movie...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.79,0:18:41.25,English-480P,,0,0,0,,No, stop it.\NI can't do it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.30,0:18:45.86,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Trier's movies are very arty-farty,\NI guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.90,0:18:50.46,English-480P,,0,0,0,,But Trier is an extremely\Ninsecure man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.50,0:18:56.77,English-480P,,0,0,0,,When he meets someone like me\Nwho isn't, he attaches himself to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.81,0:19:00.94,English-480P,,0,0,0,,He calls me and says,\N"What do I do? I don't want to fly."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.98,0:19:05.38,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I tell him,\N"Goddamn it, Trier. Drive!"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.42,0:19:11.09,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You don't get that look from the\Nothers, "She's won a lot of awards"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.13,0:19:15.03,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- You'll have to ask them.\N- You don't feel it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.06,0:19:17.83,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I think I choose to shut it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.87,0:19:21.80,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Hasn't Trier won more awards\Nthan me? He must have.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.37,0:19:27.40,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say I'm his mentor\Nor coach. I'm more a kind of rock
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.44,0:19:33.21,English-480P,,0,0,0,,on which he can place\Nhis film genius, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.25,0:19:37.62,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- You bring Trier into a new era?\N- No, he does that himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.65,0:19:43.85,English-480P,,0,0,0,,But we all know that if Iron Maiden\Nplay a concert in Edinburgh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.89,0:19:47.59,English-480P,,0,0,0,,they do the performing,\Nbut how did they get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.63,0:19:52.50,English-480P,,0,0,0,,With your enormous\Nmental resources...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.53,0:19:56.30,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- I think it's safe to say that?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.34,0:20:00.90,English-480P,,0,0,0,,The resources that you have,\Nin this situation as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.94,0:20:04.78,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Right now? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.81,0:20:10.68,English-480P,,0,0,0,,If you were to draw on that to give\NLars von Trier some advice
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.72,0:20:15.42,English-480P,,0,0,0,,to take with him\Non his journey,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.46,0:20:21.16,English-480P,,0,0,0,,what would it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.20,0:20:25.69,English-480P,,0,0,0,,"When you can't be like me, Lars,\Njust be yourself."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.94,0:20:31.53,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.57,0:20:34.51,English-480P,,0,0,0,,What's been\Nyour best advice to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.54,0:20:37.53,English-480P,,0,0,0,,It must have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.58,0:20:41.24,English-480P,,0,0,0,,"Deep breaths, Lars.\NJust get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.28,0:20:45.91,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Forget about doing\Nnew things all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.95,0:20:47.94,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Drop it. Let's have some fun."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.99,0:20:54.76,English-480P,,0,0,0,,When people look back at my films\Nin a hundred years' time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.80,0:21:01.56,English-480P,,0,0,0,,they'll probably say, "Bloody hell!\NThat guy knew what he was doing."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.60,0:21:06.73,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I'll just go and check\Nthat Iben is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.77,0:21:09.87,English-480P,,0,0,0,,She's got the car keys, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.91,0:21:16.15,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Don't you have any more questions?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.18,0:21:18.98,English-480P,,0,0,0,,We're just acting, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.02,0:21:22.55,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- Are you acting?\N- Yes. Couldn't you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.59,0:21:28.22,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- No.\N- Great acting. I really tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.84,0:21:41.90,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You've experienced it for yourself.\NThe insight into the world of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.94,0:21:46.14,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Powerlessness, power.\NJoy, enthusiasm, feelings... fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.18,0:21:51.78,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Reality, parallel reality...\NThank you for watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.82,0:22:00.39,English-480P,,0,0,0,,When you turn up in the morning,\Nready to shoot some scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.43,0:22:05.30,English-480P,,0,0,0,,it's like entering...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.33,0:22:09.70,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- different rooms.\N- What rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.74,0:22:14.61,English-480P,,0,0,0,,And one of those rooms\Nthat you're constantly in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.64,0:22:20.01,English-480P,,0,0,0,,is the room filled with fear,\NI guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.05,0:22:24.11,English-480P,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to do\Nthe interview that we agreed on,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.15,0:22:29.45,English-480P,,0,0,0,,you can say whatever\Nyou want. I'm leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.49,0:22:33.09,English-480P,,0,0,0,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.13,0:22:37.46,English-480P,,0,0,0,,You can't help laughing\Nwhen you're fearful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.50,0:22:40.49,English-480P,,0,0,0,,That's perfect. Brilliant.\NCut!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.57,0:25:55.56,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Why does he ask me that?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.18,0:29:04.11,English-480P,,0,0,0,,There was a bit more nonsense\Nin this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.15,0:29:06.91,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- I'm so involved with my work.\N- That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.95,0:29:09.94,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- "Pip."\N- "Pip."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.99,0:29:11.78,English-480P,,0,0,0,,He's fabulous.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.53,0:29:21.22,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Let me just have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.55,0:32:36.08,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- And this one is all of the text?\N- Yes, it's those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.13,0:32:38.22,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I'll get these onto some cardboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.26,0:32:43.10,English-480P,,0,0,0,,"And even though I may seem\Nlike a reflection, this film is not."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.13,0:32:50.47,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I'm happy with it.\NThat's a punch right in their faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.51,0:32:55.31,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Put it there,\Nand I'll go up and have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.34,0:32:58.54,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Put one here by my finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.58,0:33:01.57,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- That's nothing.\N- There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.76,0:33:16.03,English-480P,,0,0,0,,I'd like a movement going\Ndiagonally across the windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.20,0:33:22.36,English-480P,,0,0,0,,This is some toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.40,0:33:29.07,English-480P,,0,0,0,,If this looks odd already, please stay,\Nbecause it won't be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.60,0:36:33.09,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- That's good.\N- It's super! That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.57,0:37:09.27,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- 13 degrees to the left.\N- That won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.31,0:37:15.08,English-480P,,0,0,0,,- It's the wrong direction.\N- Let's have a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.95,0:37:53.28,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Tilt down 11 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.32,0:37:58.78,English-480P,,0,0,0,,And 33 centimeters to the left.\NYou'll like this, Lars.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.83,0:38:03.56,English-480P,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're happy, I'm happy.
